				<p>After reading through the comments of your baked berry desserts, I was thinking about why some berries sink and other don&#8217;t and while some stay firm and others turn to mush. I think it may have to do with the differences in the berries themselves. Depending on the variety, time of year, and the freshness, blueberries (or any fruit) can be small, big, soft, hard, etc. Some varieties may have more liquid in them and others may be drier. I&#8217;d love to do an experiment, but it would be tricky trying to get different varieties of the same fruit.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
<li class="commentbody" id="comment-308265">
