<li class="commentbody" id="comment-807502">
			<cite>laurie</cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-807502" title="">July 28, 2011</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">385</div>

				<p>To keep the berries from all sinking (and I use one cup in the batter and one cup on top), here&#8217;s my tip. Spread up to 1/2 the batter into the pan before folding in the berries. Use enough so you can spread the batter without it pulling up and away from the floured surface. Then, fold the berries into the remaining batter and add to the pan.<br />
I always add more sugar, and it takes much less time to bake in my oven. I starting checking after 25-30 minutes.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
